data.name: Tetrad #2: Four objects collections of objects
data.description:
## Task
Write a function that takes two numbers and returns four items in the list. 

The first item will be an tuple, like this ```(n1, n1 + 1, ..., n2)```, sort order should be ascending.

The second item will be a list, like this ```[n1, n1 + 1, ..., n2]```, sort order should be ascending. 

The third item will be a dict, like this ```{n1: n1, n1 + 1: n1 + 1, ..., n2: n2}```. 

The fourth item will be a set, like this ```{n1, n1 + 1, ..., n2}```.

## Input

Integer number n1.

Integer number n2.

n2 >= n1

## Output

An array of four objects.

If the value of one of the input variables will not be an integer type, function should return None.

## Example
For n1 = 3 and n2 = 5, the output should be ```[(3, 4, 5), [3, 4, 5], {3: 3, 4: 4, 5: 5}, {3, 4, 5}]```.

For n1 = 1 and n2 = 4, the output should be ```[(1, 2, 3, 4), [1, 2, 3, 4], {1: 1, 2: 2, 3: 3, 4: 4}, {1, 2, 3, 4}]```.

For n1 = 4 and n2 = 3, the output should be ```None```.

## Collection
[Tetrad](https://www.codewars.com/collections/tetrad)
